Q3.Write a PHP script to change the preferences of your web page like font style, 
font size,font color,background color using cookie.Display selected setting on next web page and actual 
implementation (with new settings) on third page.

1stPage
<html>
<body>
<form action="Q3_1.php" method="POST">
Enter Font Style : <input type="text" name="t1"><hr>
Enter Font Size : <input type="text" name="t2"><hr>
Enter Color : <input type="text" name="t3"><hr>
Enter Background-Color : <input type="text" name="t4"><hr>
<input type="Submit" Value="Next">
</form>
</body>
</html>


2ndPage
<?php
	$style=$_POST["t1"];
	$size=$_POST["t2"];
	$color=$_POST["t3"];
	$bgcolor=$_POST["t4"];
	
	setcookie("style",$style,time()+3600);
	setcookie("size",$size,time()+3600);
	setcookie("color",$color,time()+3600);
	setcookie("bgcolor",$bgcolor,time()+3600);
	
	echo "<br>Style is: ".$style;
	echo "<br>Size is: ".$size;
	echo"<br>Color is: ".$color;
	echo "<br>BgColor is: ".$bgcolor;
	
?>
<html>
<body>
<a href="Q3_2.php">OK</a>
</body>
</html>


3rdPage
<?php
	$style=$_COOKIE["style"];
	$size=$_COOKIE["size"];
	$color=$_COOKIE["color"];
	$bgcolor=$_COOKIE["bgcolor"];
	
	echo "<br><font style=$style>Hello ";
	echo "<br><font size =$size>Hello ";
	echo "<br><font color =$color>Hello ";
	echo "<br><body bgcolor =$bgcolor>";
?>
